rComments: Nice guy, explains the content well and his tests are fair. Lectures are good considering how inherently dry and heavy the course content is. Made the content interesting enough for me to be continuing my studies of abstract algebra beyond his course. Good communication and useful announcements are posted consistently on portal

Seems very distant at first but great guy once you actually get to know him! Course isn't about memorizing theorems, rather it's about understanding concepts. That being said, his tests still have a large "computation" component so it's actually pretty easy if you do all the homework
Selim seems a little aloof but I think that's just his personality. His tests are fair and he seems to want his students to succeed. I think he might be sick or malnourished though...
Worst professor I have ever met at UofT. IRRESPONSIBLE.
He did try to alert us, cut him some slack
Wasted 40 minutes sitting around. Talk about first impressions...
